L. A. WALLACE, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6904. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 21, 1934. Wm. C. Hodges, of Tallahassee, Fla., for appellant. John W. Holland, U. S. Atty., of Jacksonville, Fla.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and WALKER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This is an appeal from a judgment of conviction for violations of the National ProKbition Act (27 USCA § 1 et seq.). Upon authority of United States v. Chambers, 54 S. Ct. 434, 78 L. Ed. -, opinion filed February 5, 1934, the judgment is reversed and annulled.
